photo.title: Matsuyama Castle

description._content:
Matsuyama Castle was originally constructed in 1603 by Kato Yoshiaki on the peak of Mount Katsuyama. The large, five-story tenshu was later moved to Aizu when he was transfered there in 1627. After the Matsudaira took over rulership of the castle, they rebuilt the tenshu in 1642. The current castle, though damaged during WWII dates back to the mid-1800's.
 
Matsuyama Castle. Matsuyama, Ehime.

description._content: Day 8, Nov 11 2015: We enjoyed a 9-hour tour of Kyoto's cultural and historic attractions - We visited top city highlights such as Nijo Castle, Kinkaku-ji Temple and the Heian Shrine. - We explored the Kyoto Imperial Palace with our guide, once residence of Japan’s Imperial family. - We checked out the Thousand Armed Kannon and the legion of 1,000 life-size statues at the Buddhist temple of Sanju-Sangendo Hall - We visited the Kiyomizu Temple and enjoyed panoramic views over Kyoto from the temple’s terrace

photo.title: At the water spout

description._content: On our first day in Kyoto, we walked up to Kiyomizudera Temple which was near to where we were staying. It was a Sunday afternoon at the end of the autumn leaves season. I was surprised at how many Japanese - male and female though mostly female - were wearing traditional clothes. We saw more here than anywhere else. I wondered if it was because it was a Sunday and also the last of the autumn colours season. There were lots of selfies being taken :-)

photo.tags: autumn winter people leaves japan kyoto colours kimono japanesegirls traditionaldress higashiyama 2015 kiyomizuderatemple

photo.title: Day 13: Into the Clouds at Miyajima Japan

description._content: Day 13, Nov 16 2015: After spending a romantic and super relaxing night in Miyajima we headed up the rope way to check out Mount Misen. Unfortunately it ended up being rainy and cloudy so once we got to the top there was no site to see. We were in the middle of a big cloud! After Mount Misen we spent the majority of the day traveling. We took the ferry back to the main land and took trains all the way back to Tokyo. Once in Tokyo we wondered around the area of our new hotel. The hotel is 30 floors and massive, we had an amazing view of the city.

photo.title: Afraid of Yuki-onna

description._content: Snowstorm in Tokyo Album Yuki-onna (雪女?, snow woman) is a spirit or yōkai in Japanese folklore. She is a popular figure in Japanese literature, manga, film , and animation. She may also go by such names as yuki-musume "snow girl",[1] yuki-onago "snow wench", yukijorō "snow harlot",[1] yuki anesa "snow sis'", yuki-omba "snow granny or snow nanny",[2] yukinba "snow hag" (Ehime),[2] yukifuri-baba(?) "snowfall hag"[1](Nagano).[2]

photo.title: Winter Sunset at Ihama Rocky Beach

description._content: Happy new year Guys! I wish you a fantastic 2016 :) - - - Ihama Rocky Beach is located in Minamiizu of Japan, and you can watch the sunset here only for winter 60 days. Exposure 0.5 second - 1 Raw-shot picture. (Not doing the synthesis and HDR processing) 新年おめでとうございます。 本年もどうぞよろしくお願い致します (^^ 【南伊豆・伊浜海岸での夕日】 このカットは3年ぶりのショットになります。去る12月18日、暖かくて空の様子が良さそうなので出かけてみました。 ここでの夕日は冬至の前後がベストになりますが、冬はたいてい西（正面）からの強風に見舞われ撮影どころではありません（波しぶきで3分以内にレンズが真っ白）。その西風が収まり、しっとりと暖かくなった日は燃えるような空になることがあり、例年待ち望んでいます。ここ2年間は温暖化のせいか、あの素晴らしい夕焼けが見られません。。 data: Taken on Dec 18 2015, 16:40 in Minami-Izu. description._content:
Myojoyama Park
明星山公園

This is my trial of composite photograph.
The city light is Fujinomiya city.
10 airplanes passed with in 30 minutes.

一度試してみたかった比較明合成の写真です。
ちょっと明るく潰れてしまった街の光は富士宮市です。
30分間に通過した飛行機は10機。

月明かりもなかったので富士山も潰れてしまいました。
飛行機のいない時間帯を狙うとなると
耐久戦になりそうです。

[composite of 90 shots, 30min]
Fujinomiya city, Shizuoka pref, Japan
